            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>pulled</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>drained tortiglioni</strong>, your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add a splash of <strong>starchy</strong> <strong>pasta water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>chicken & tomato tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p><p>Cut the <strong>zested lemon[s]</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
